You could force the detection by using the `ChangeDetectorRef`

    import { ..., ChangeDetectorRef } from &#39;@angular/core&#39;;

Add it on your constructor

    constructor(private _cdr: ChangeDetectorRef) {...}

And in your child component

    this._cdr.markForCheck();
    // or if not working
    this._cdr.detectChanges()

Another thing, JQuery is not recommanded with Angular. If you want to use modal in your project, you should check [Angular material modal][1] or make your own modal component.


  [1]: https://material.angular.io/components/dialog/overview

